      <p>
        <s>In scene 3 of the play <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="title">Disgraced, Scene 3</ref> by <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="author">Ayad Akhtar</ref>, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref>, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac's</ref> wife, who also is <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir's</ref> work partner catches <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref> and <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> <add>(<ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir's</ref> wife)</add> kissing, right after she told <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> about her getting the job <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> wanted to have for a long time.</s>
        <s>He accuses that she stole her job and also destroys his marriage.</s>
        <s>But <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> does not listen to him because she is shocked by his husband cheating and denying it.</s>
        <s>On their way out <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> expresses that <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> can't be trusted, because of his double identity.</s>
        <s><ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> takes his time to realize what happened and asks <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> about her affair with <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref>.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>After she admitted her being unloyal <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> freaks out and beats <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> until she bleeds, without realizing what he is actually doing.</s>
      </p>
